Legal
Conflict materials statement
Conflict materials statement
Conflict materials (specifically Gold, Tin Tantalum and Tungsten) are not sourced directly by Megger from any areas of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) or any adjoining countries where the revenue of such material may directly or indirectly finance armed conflict and civil war.
Megger Group implements a Supplier Code of Conduct which specifically addresses the use of conflict materials and can confirm that no products manufactured within the Megger manufacturing facilities contain such materials.
Vendors shall have policies to reasonably ensure that materials consumed in the manufacturing process does not directly or indirectly finance terrorism, armed groups or perpetrators who seriously breach any individuals humans rights. Vendors are required upon request to make their supply chain of material available for inspection.
This policy is issued by, and owned by, the Megger Group Board. No deviations may be made from it without written Board approval.
Dr Andrew Dodds
- Group Director
